signatureAbility.signatureDescription: Elite pass rushers are a mix of strength, speed, and tenacity. When they enter the zone, this ability increases their win rate and block shed speed against one-on-one pass blocks.
Defenders with this ability use faster, more dominant pass rush moves while rushing from the edge of the defense.
Defenders with this ability can still tackle effectively while trying to strip the football.
Defenders with this ability can apply pressure to the quarterback from a greater distance.
Players with this ability avoid any ratings penalties associated with playing outside of their primary position
Players with this ability will recover from the effects of Wear and Tear and fatigue at an increased rate between plays.
Players with this ability are much less likely to be fooled by WR runoffs
Defenders with this ability have better conservative/dive tackling, are rarely faked out by ballcarrier moves, and cannot be faked out when user-controlled.
Defenders with this ability force more catch knockouts and react quicker in any flat zone coverage, less than 10 yards from the LoS and outside the hash marks.
Defenders with this ability have a larger timing window for landing Perfect Hit Sticks
Receivers with this ability catch more consistently while catching passes less than 10 yards from the LoS, outside the numbers
Players with this ability are more likely to succeed at and attempt diving catches and swats.
Ballcarriers with this ability are effective at recovering from attempted tackles regardless of their current stamina.
